## The Mathematical Objects Used by ML-KEM

ML-KEM uses polynomial and modular arithmetic.

Some important constants and parameters include:

```text
n = 256
q = 3329
```

At a high level:

* `n` relates to the degree of the polynomials used.
* `q` is the modulus used for arithmetic.
* The algorithm works with polynomial vectors and matrices.
* The parameter `k` changes depending on the selected ML-KEM security level.

ML-KEM has three parameter sets:

| Parameter Set | Security Category | k Value |
| ------------- | ----------------: | ------: |
| ML-KEM-512    |        Category 1 |       2 |
| ML-KEM-768    |        Category 3 |       3 |
| ML-KEM-1024   |        Category 5 |       4 |

A higher parameter set generally means stronger security but larger keys, larger ciphertexts, and more computation.

---

## The Three ML-KEM Parameter Sets

ML-KEM defines three parameter sets.

| Parameter Set | Encapsulation Key | Decapsulation Key |  Ciphertext | Shared Secret |
| ------------- | ----------------: | ----------------: | ----------: | ------------: |
| ML-KEM-512    |         800 bytes |       1,632 bytes |   768 bytes |      32 bytes |
| ML-KEM-768    |       1,184 bytes |       2,400 bytes | 1,088 bytes |      32 bytes |
| ML-KEM-1024   |       1,568 bytes |       3,168 bytes | 1,568 bytes |      32 bytes |

The shared secret is always 32 bytes, or 256 bits.

The larger parameter sets increase security strength but also increase key and ciphertext sizes.

A practical way to think about the choices:

| Parameter Set | Practical Meaning                             |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| ML-KEM-512    | Smaller and faster, lower security category   |
| ML-KEM-768    | Common balanced choice                        |
| ML-KEM-1024   | Larger and stronger, higher security category |

In many real-world protocol discussions, ML-KEM-768 is often treated as the default balanced option, but final selection depends on the system, security requirements, compliance needs, and protocol profile.

