## Clean Mental Model

Use this mental model:

```text
Diffie-Hellman:
Both parties mix private and public values to agree on a shared secret.

ML-KEM:
One party uses the other party's encapsulation key to create a ciphertext and shared secret.
The other party uses the decapsulation key to recover the same shared secret.

Certificates/signatures:
Prove who the party is.

Symmetric encryption:
Uses the derived keys to protect the actual data.
```

The simplest version:

```text
ML-KEM helps two parties get the same secret.

It does not prove identity.

It does not encrypt all data directly.

It is a post-quantum key establishment building block.
```

